<h2>Update RAG status</h2>

<p>The RAG (Red, Amber, Green) status indicates the overall health of your project. To update it:</p>

<ol>
    <li>Go to the project details page</li>
    <li>Click on the <strong>RAG tracking</strong> tab</li>
    <li>Select the appropriate RAG status:
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Green</strong> - On track, no issues</li>
            <li><strong>Amber-Green</strong> - Mostly on track, minor issues</li>
            <li><strong>Amber</strong> - Some concerns, needs attention</li>
            <li><strong>Amber-Red</strong> - Significant concerns, at risk</li>
            <li><strong>Red</strong> - Major issues, delivery at risk</li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>Provide a justification explaining why this status has been chosen</li>
    <li>If the status is not Green, provide a "Path to green" describing how you plan to resolve issues</li>
    <li>Click <strong>Update RAG status</strong> to save</li>
</ol>

<h3>Best practice</h3>
<ul>
    <li>Update RAG status regularly (at least monthly)</li>
    <li>Be honest about project health - early identification of issues helps prevent problems</li>
    <li>Use the justification field to explain context and any mitigating actions</li>
    <li>Keep the "Path to green" updated as you work through issues</li>
</ul>

<p>The RAG status history is tracked, so you can see how the status has changed over time.</p>

